Analysis of Chicks on a Diet

Dhivya Iyer

7/30/2021

Source and description of data

https://stat.ethz.ch/R-manual/R-devel/library/datasets/html/ChickWeight.html

Objective

Compare how effective the different diets were in supporting the growth of the chicks.

Setting up my environment

Explore the data

Plot the data the get a sense of how the chicks weights changes over time

ggplot(ChickWeight)+
  geom_point(aes(x=Time,y=weight,color=Chick))+
  facet_wrap(~Diet)

ggplot(ChickWeight)+
  geom_line(aes(x=Time,y=weight,color=Chick))+
  facet_wrap(~Diet)

Analyze the data

Plot the average weights of the chicks on each diet over time

avg_weights<-ChickWeight %>% 
  filter(Diet==1) %>% 
  group_by(Time) %>% 
  summarize(avg_weight=mean(weight))

avg_weights<-ChickWeight %>% 
  filter(Diet==2) %>% 
  group_by(Time) %>% 
  summarize(avg_weight=mean(weight)) %>% 
  merge(avg_weights,by="Time") %>% 
  rename(avg_weight1=avg_weight.x,avg_weight2=avg_weight.y)

avg_weights<-ChickWeight %>% 
  filter(Diet==3) %>% 
  group_by(Time) %>% 
  summarize(avg_weight=mean(weight)) %>% 
  merge(avg_weights,by="Time")

avg_weights<-ChickWeight %>% 
  filter(Diet==4) %>% 
  group_by(Time) %>% 
  summarize(avg_weight=mean(weight)) %>% 
  merge(avg_weights,by="Time") %>% 
  rename(avg_weight3=avg_weight.x,avg_weight4=avg_weight.y)

ggplot(avg_weights)+
  scale_x_continuous(name="Days Since Birth",breaks=avg_weights$Time)+
  scale_y_continuous(name="Average Weight",breaks=c(0,50,100,150,200,250,300))+
  labs(title="Average weights of chicks on different diets over time",y="Average Weight")+
  geom_line(aes(x=Time,y=avg_weight1),color=1)+
  annotate("text",x=22,y=214.7,label="Diet 1",color=1)+
  geom_line(aes(x=Time,y=avg_weight2),color=2)+
  annotate("text",x=22,y=177.8,label="Diet 2",color=2)+
  geom_line(aes(x=Time,y=avg_weight3),color=3)+
  annotate("text",x=22,y=238.6,label="Diet 3",color=3)+
  geom_line(aes(x=Time,y=avg_weight4),color=4)+
  annotate("text",x=22,y=270.3,label="Diet 4",color=4)

Diet 4 was the most effective in making the chicks grow the most and diet 2 was the least effective. Diets 3 and 4 crossed over between days 12 and 14.

Plot the standard deviations of the chicks weights on each diet over time

sd_weights<-ChickWeight %>% 
  filter(Diet==1) %>% 
  group_by(Time) %>% 
  summarize(sd_weight=sd(weight))

sd_weights<-ChickWeight %>% 
  filter(Diet==2) %>% 
  group_by(Time) %>% 
  summarize(sd_weight=sd(weight)) %>% 
  merge(sd_weights,by="Time") %>% 
  rename(sd_weight1=sd_weight.x,sd_weight2=sd_weight.y)

sd_weights<-ChickWeight %>% 
  filter(Diet==3) %>% 
  group_by(Time) %>% 
  summarize(sd_weight=sd(weight)) %>% 
  merge(sd_weights,by="Time")

sd_weights<-ChickWeight %>% 
  filter(Diet==4) %>% 
  group_by(Time) %>% 
  summarize(sd_weight=sd(weight)) %>% 
  merge(sd_weights,by="Time") %>% 
  rename(sd_weight3=sd_weight.x,sd_weight4=sd_weight.y)

ggplot(sd_weights)+
  scale_x_continuous(name="Days Since Birth",breaks=sd_weights$Time)+
  geom_line(aes(x=Time,y=sd_weight1),color=1)+
  annotate("text",x=22,y=78.1,label="Diet 1",color=1)+
  geom_line(aes(x=Time,y=sd_weight2),color=2)+
  annotate("text",x=22,y=58.7,label="Diet 2",color=2)+
  geom_line(aes(x=Time,y=sd_weight3),color=3)+
  annotate("text",x=22,y=43.35,label="Diet 3",color=3)+
  geom_line(aes(x=Time,y=sd_weight4),color=4)+
  annotate("text",x=22,y=71.6,label="Diet 4",color=4)+
  labs(title="Standard Deviation of chick weights on different diets over time",y="Standard deviation of Weight")

The weights of the chicks vary the most in diet 1 and the least in diet 3. The standard deviations of diets 2 and 4 crossed over on day 16.

Now lets explore how the distrubutions of the chicks weights changed over time.

ChickWeight %>% 
  filter(Time==0) %>% 
  ggplot()+
  geom_violin(aes(x=Time,y=weight,fill=Diet))+
  geom_boxplot(aes(x=Time,y=weight,fill=Diet),width=0.3)+
  geom_point(aes(x=Time,y=weight,))+
  scale_x_discrete(labels = NULL, breaks = NULL)+
  labs(title="Weights of Chicks on diets",subtitle="Day 0",y="Weight",x="")+
  facet_grid(~Diet)
